t the despair, Laura. I can take the despair. It's the hope I can't stand. ~ Brian Stimpson, Clockwise\n\n- John\n|\nAll in all, he thought it was a bad idea to get involved with the woman investigating his ex's possible suicide with intent to haunt.\n\n- Marybeth Niederkorn, Small Town Tales: Volume 1\n|\nLosing excess fats through exercise is important, but losing useless friends is urgent. Treat urgent things first!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Let's Go to the Next Level\n|\nThe final magnificent spark of a firework is only the last seconds of the fall. Though it’s invisible to most, it’s the way up that creates all the impact.\n\n- Charlotte\n|\nAre we not witnessing a strange tableau of survival whenever a bird alights on the head of a crocodile, bringing together the evolutionary offspring of Triassic and Jurassic?\n\n- Annalee Newitz, Scatter, Adapt, and Remember: How Humans Will Survive a Mass Extinction\n|\nThe enduring attraction of war is this: Even with its destruction and carnage it can give us what we long for in life. It can give us purpose, meaning, a reason for living.\n\n- Chris Hedges, War Is a Force That Gives Us Meaning\n|\nTo succeed in life you need five things – a burning desire, a willingness to do whatever it takes, wisdom, incredible effort, and a commitment to never-ending improvement.\n\n- Mensah\n|\n‎'Life's book is hard to understand: Why couldst thou not remain atschool?\n\n- Charles\n|\nI long for you; I who usually longs without longing, as though I am unconscious and absorbed in neutrality and apathy, really, utterly long for every bit of you.\n\n- Franz Kafka, Letters to Milena\n|\nWhat do you want? What do you want?...To see the world burn, and a new one be born from the ashes…\n\n- S.R. Crawford, No Secrets: Remastered\n|\nDance is a game of extreme emotions and freedom of the soul, where nothing is ever the same.\n\n- Sergei\n|\nSuccess is living life with all of its songs and melodies, triumphs and tragedies.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI like to read fairytales. They make my imagination go wild, and I wander in fairyland.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you take too long in deciding what to do with your life, you'll find you've done it.\n\n- George\n|\nKnowledge is a tool, and like all tools, its impact is in the hands of the user.\n\n- Dan Brown, The Lost Symbol\n|\n...when pain is over, the remembrance of it often becomes a pleasure.\n\n- Jane Austen, Persuasion\n|\nHe was so far away now, or maybe he just looked distant because we were imaging different things for our future.\n\n- Alexandra Kleeman, You Too Can Have a Body Like Mine\n|\nYou lived what anybody gets, Bernie. You got a lifetime. No more. No less.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, Brief Lives\n|\nTo find your self, get lost is the search of knowledge and wisdom.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI love you, even if there isn’t any me, or any love, or even any life. I love you.\n\n- Zelda\n|\nYou cannot fully wrap your mind around God, so better to fully wrap God around your mind.\n\n- James Randall Robison, God Wants You to Be Happy\n|\nWhat sets humans apart from animals is that we have to walk around saying how smart we are, and animals just live their lives.\n\n- Chanctetinyea\n|\nShe was a fool, and so am I, and so is anyone who thinks he sees what God is Doing, [writes Bokonon].\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., Cat's Cradle\n|\nSorrow is how we learn to love. Your heart isn't breaking. It hurts because it's getting larger. The larger it gets, the more love it holds.\n\n- Rita Mae Brown, Riding Shotgun\n|\nLife is funny. Things change, people change, but you will always be you, so stay true to yourself and never sacrifice who you are for anyone.\n\n- Zayn\n|\nHope-that unshakable golden belief that things can get better- is why I'm here talking to you now. Without it, we are nothing.\n\n- Alexander\n|\nThey say a person needs just three things to be truly happy in this world: someone to love, something to do, and something to hope for.\n\n- Tom\n|\nGive me golf clubs, fresh air and 